cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.HC 

The paper focuses on using machine learning methods for Alzheimer's disease classification based on MRI images. Specifically, it proposes to learn deep convolutional image features using unsupervised and supervised learning, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of deep learning also suggests the possibility of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE) being relevant sub-categories. Finally, the paper also discusses the potential impact on healthcare (cs.HC) by improving the accuracy of Alzheimer's disease diagnosis.
